---
description: No blank lines between properties on Options/DTO-style types (C#)
globs: **/*Options.cs,**/*Dto.cs,**/*Request.cs,**/*Response.cs,**/*Settings.cs
alwaysApply: false
---

# Data model property spacing

For **property-bag** types (options, settings, DTOs, API request/response shapes, simple records used only as data carriers), **do not put empty lines between consecutive properties**.

Keep a single blank line before the **first** property only if needed after type declaration / attributes; otherwise keep the body compact.

## Examples

```csharp
// ❌ BAD
public sealed class KafkaConsumerOptions
{
    public string BootstrapServers { get; set; } = string.Empty;

    public string GroupId { get; set; } = string.Empty;

    public string Topic { get; set; } = string.Empty;
}

// ✅ GOOD
public sealed class KafkaConsumerOptions
{
    public string BootstrapServers { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string GroupId { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Topic { get; set; } = string.Empty;
}
```

## Scope

- Applies to types in the matched globs that are **mostly auto-properties or simple fields**.
- **Does not** override intentional spacing in classes with lots of behavior (methods, nested types); those files are usually outside these globs.
